definition.value: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is 2-oxobutanoic acid with double bond at position 3.
A spirostanyl glycoside that consists of the trisaccharide alpha-L-Rha-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Rha-(1->2)]-beta-D-Glc attached to position 3 of diosgenin via a glycosidic linkage.
An aminoalkylpyridine that is pyridine substituted by a ethanamino group at position 2.
A steroid saponin that is protodioscin lacking the 26-O-glucosyl moiety.
A sulfonium compound that is dimethysulfonium with a 3-oxopropyl substituent.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that consists of a beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcNAc moiety linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
A pyrimidone that is cytosine substituted by an ethyl group at position 3.
A taxane diterpenoid that is 3'-N-debenzoyltaxol which is lacking the 2-hydroxy group.
A carboxyalkanesulfonic acid that is the C-sulfo derivative of propanoic acid.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that consists of a beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-alpha-D-GlcNAc moiety linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that consists of a beta-D-Glc-(1->3)-alpha-D-GlcNAc moiety linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
An octadecatrienoyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of alpha-linolenoyl-CoA.
A class of small RNA molecules which are comprised of approximately 150 nucleotides and which are found within the nucleus of eukaryotic cells.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that consists of an alpha-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalNAc moiety linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (11Z)-3-oxoicosa-11-enoic acid.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that consists of a beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalNAc moiety linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
A monoterpenoid that is furan in which the hydrogen at position 3 is replaced by a 4-methylpent-3-en-1-yl group. A defensive allomone of thrips that has a flowery, citrus-like flavour.
A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that consists of an alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalNAc moiety linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.

A polyprenyl phospho oligosaccharide that consists of the pentasaccharide alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-GalNAc linked via a diphospho group to ditrans,octacis-undecaprenol.
A 2-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)-L-histidine dizwitterion arising from transfer of two protons from the carboxy to the amino groups of 2-[(3S)-3-amino-3-carboxypropyl]-L-histidine.
A 2-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)-L-histidine in which position 3 on the side-chain has S-configuration.
A monocarboxylic acid that is the 5-chloro derivative of  4-hydroxy-2-oxopentanoic acid.
A GDP-hexose having 4-amino-4,6-dideoxy-alpha-D-mannose as the hexose fragment.
A thioadenosine that is adenosine with the hydroxy group at C-5' substituted with an ethylthio (ethylsulfanyl) group.
A GDP-hexose having N-acetyl-alpha-D-perosamine as the hexose fragment.
A  piperidinemonocarboxylic acid that is pipecolic acid with a hydroxy substituent at position 5.
An L-tryptophan derivative that is L-tryptophan with a methoxy substituent at position 5.
A CDP-glycerol that is 2,3-bis-O-(phytanyl)-sn-glycerol (archaeol) having a CDP moiety attached at position 1.
A dipeptide formed from two L-histidine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-lysine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-methionine residues.
A 3-oxo-fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (11Z,14Z,17Z)-3-oxoicosatrienoyl-CoA.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-proline residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-serine residues.
A 16-carboxy-Delta(13)-17,18,19,20-tetranor-leukotriene E4 in which the double bond at position 13-14 has E-configuration.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-tryptophan residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-tyrosine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-histidine and L-valine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and L-arginine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and L-alanine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and L-asparagine residues.
An  oxopurine that is  guanine with an oxo group at position 8 and a methyl substituent at position 7.
A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and L-glutamine residues.
A dipeptide formed from L-isoleucine and glycine residues.
A dipeptide formed from two L-isoleucine residues.

A monounsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (11Z)-eicosenoyl-CoA.
An acyl-CoA(4-) arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (13Z)-3-oxodocosenoyl-CoA.
